      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Milos Stanisavljevic</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:242px;\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/milosstanisavljevic/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/ba/MilosStanisavljevic.jpg/240px-MilosStanisavljevic.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"240\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/b/ba/MilosStanisavljevic.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:MilosStanisavljevic.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Milos Stanisavljevic  <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Milos Stanisavljevic</b> (Miloš Stanisavljević),<br />\na Serbian electrical engineer holding a <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diplom\">Diplom</a> from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Belgrade\">University of Belgrade</a> in 2004, and a Ph.D. on <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microelectronics\">microelectronics</a> from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89cole_Polytechnique_F%C3%A9d%C3%A9rale_de_Lausanne\">École Polytechnique Fédérale de Lausanne</a> in 2009 <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>, \nactually visiting scientist at <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IBM_Zurich_Research_Laboratory\">IBM Zurich Research Laboratory</a>. \nHis professional interests include <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microelectronics\">microelectronics</a> and <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nanoelectronics\">nanoelectronics</a>, in particular he is researching on <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multi-level_cell\">multi-level cell</a> <a href=\"/Memory\" title=\"Memory\">memory</a>, his private interests include computer chess. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Computer_Chess\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Computer Chess</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Selected_Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Publications</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#2005_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2005 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#2015_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2015 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#2009\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2009</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#2010\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#2011\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2011</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#2013\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2013</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-12\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Computer_Chess\">Computer Chess</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Milos_Stanisavljevic&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Computer Chess\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>Milos Stanisavljevic is a formidable expert of the <a href=\"/Ippolit\" title=\"Ippolit\">Ippolit</a> family of engines <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>, and advocate of Ippolit's originality, despite his note it used ideas from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reverse_engineering\">reverse engineering</a> <a href=\"/Rybka\" title=\"Rybka\">Rybka 3</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>. He further stands sentinel <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> over a stable <a href=\"/RobboLito\" title=\"RobboLito\">RobboLito</a> release under the <a href=\"/Free_Software_Foundation#GPL\" title=\"Free Software Foundation\">GNU GPL</a>, which is due to misuse no longer available for download <sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>. \nFurther, along with <a href=\"/Norman_Schmidt\" title=\"Norman Schmidt\">Norman Schmidt</a>, Milos Stanisavljevic worked on <a href=\"/Fire\" title=\"Fire\">Fire</a>, derived from <a href=\"/IvanHoe\" title=\"IvanHoe\">IvanHoe</a> and the <a href=\"/Ippolit\" title=\"Ippolit\">Ippolit</a> series of programs <sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publications\">Selected Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Milos_Stanisavljevic&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2005_...\">2005 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Milos_Stanisavljevic&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: 2005 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Milos Stanisavljevic</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=cg4HBEYAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Alexandre Schmid</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=TyMAGtYAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Yusuf Leblebici</a> (<b>2005</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.springerlink.com/content/604l6k0r1215037k/\">A Methodology for Reliability Enhancement of Nanometer-Scale Digital Systems Based on a-priori Functional Fault- Tolerance Analysis</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.informatik.uni-trier.de/~ley/db/conf/vlsi/vlsisoc2005.html#StanisavljevicSL05\">VLSI-SoC'2005</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Milos Stanisavljevic</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.org/pers/hd/g/G=uuml=rkaynak:Frank_K=\">Frank K. Gürkaynak</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=cg4HBEYAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Alexandre Schmid</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=TyMAGtYAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Yusuf Leblebici</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.org/pers/hd/g/Gabrani:Maria\">Maria Gabrani</a> (<b>2007</b>). <i>Design and Realization of a Fault-tolerant 90nm CMOS Cryptographic Engine capable of performing under Massive Defect Density</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.informatik.uni-trier.de/~ley/db/conf/glvlsi/glvlsi2007.html#StanisavljevicGSLG07\">ACM Great Lakes Symposium on VLSI'2007</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://infoscience.epfl.ch/record/109328/files/GLSVLSI204-Stanisavljevic.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Milos Stanisavljevic</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=cg4HBEYAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Alexandre Schmid</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=TyMAGtYAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Yusuf Leblebici</a> (<b>2008</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://iopscience.iop.org/0957-4484/19/46/465202\">Optimization of Nanoelectronic Systems' Reliability under Massive Defect Density using Cascaded R-fold Modular Redundancy</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://iopscience.iop.org/0957-4484/19/46\">Nanotechnology, Vol. 19, No. 46</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Milos Stanisavljevic</a> (<b>2009</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://infoscience.epfl.ch/record/133436\">On the dependability of nanoscale circuits and systems methodologies and circuit architectures</a></i>. Ph.D. thesis, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89cole_Polytechnique_F%C3%A9d%C3%A9rale_de_Lausanne\">École Polytechnique Fédérale de Lausanne</a>, advisors <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=cg4HBEYAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Alexandre Schmid</a> and <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=TyMAGtYAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Yusuf Leblebici</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Milos Stanisavljevic</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=cg4HBEYAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Alexandre Schmid</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=TyMAGtYAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Yusuf Leblebici</a> (<b>2009</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://infoscience.epfl.ch/record/128794\">Optimization of the Averaging Reliability Technique using Low Redundancy Factors for Nanoscale Technologies</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ieee.org/portal/pages/products/nanotechnology/index.html\">IEEE Transactions on Nanotechnology</a>, Vol. 8, No. 2</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010_...\">2010 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Milos_Stanisavljevic&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 2010 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Milos Stanisavljevic</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=cg4HBEYAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Alexandre Schmid</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=TyMAGtYAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Yusuf Leblebici</a> (<b>2010</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/Xplore/login.jsp?url=http%3A%2F%2Fieeexplore.ieee.org%2Fiel5%2F5629484%2F5642591%2F05642682.pdf%3Farnumber%3D5642682&amp;authDecision=-203\">Output Probability Density Functions of Logic Circuits: Modeling and Fault-tolerance Evaluation</a></i>.  <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.informatik.uni-trier.de/~ley/db/conf/vlsi/vlsisoc2010.html#StanisavljevicSL10\">VLSI-SoC'2010</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Miloš Stanisavljević</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=cg4HBEYAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Alexandre Schmid</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=TyMAGtYAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Yusuf Leblebici</a> (<b>2011</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.springer.com/engineering/circuits+%26+systems/book/978-1-4419-6216-4\">Reliability of Nanoscale Circuits and Systems: Methodologies and Circuit Architectures</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Springer_Science%2BBusiness_Media\">Springer</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=1y6pRmEAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Aravinthan Athmanathan</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Milos Stanisavljevic</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.org/pers/hd/c/Cheon:Junho\">Junho Cheon</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.org/pers/hd/k/Kang:Seokjoon\">Seokjoon Kang</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.org/pers/hd/a/Ahn:Changyong\">Changyong Ahn</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.org/pers/hd/y/Yoon:Junghyuk\">Junghyuk Yoon</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.org/pers/hd/s/Shin:Min=Chul\">Min-Chul Shin</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.org/pers/hd/k/Kim:Taekseung\">Taekseung Kim</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pers/hd/p/Papandreou:Nikolaos\">Nikolaos Papandreou</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.co.uk/citations?user=FhioCGgAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Haralampos Pozidis</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evangelos_S._Eleftheriou\">Evangelos Eleftheriou</a> (<b>2014</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/A-6-bit-drift-resilient-readout-scheme-for-Memory-Athmanathan-Stanisavljevic/072d918e90ffc33c7d07b724a27964ce6062e874\">A 6-bit drift-resilient readout scheme for multi-level Phase-Change Memory</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.org/db/conf/asscc/asscc2014.html\">A-SSCC 2014</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2015_...\">2015 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Milos_Stanisavljevic&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: 2015 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Milos Stanisavljevic</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=1y6pRmEAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Aravinthan Athmanathan</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pers/hd/p/Papandreou:Nikolaos\">Nikolaos Papandreou</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.co.uk/citations?user=FhioCGgAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Haralampos Pozidis</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evangelos_S._Eleftheriou\">Evangelos Eleftheriou</a> (<b>2015</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Phase-change-memory%3A-Feasibility-of-reliable-and-at-Stanisavljevic-Athmanathan/96eef8ca0b005c467031fe66503cbb77e6e9df34\">Phase-change memory: Feasibility of reliable multilevel-cell storage and retention at elevated temperatures</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.org/db/conf/irps/irps2015.html\">IRPS 2015</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=1y6pRmEAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Aravinthan Athmanathan</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Milos Stanisavljevic</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pers/hd/p/Papandreou:Nikolaos\">Nikolaos Papandreou</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.co.uk/citations?user=FhioCGgAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Haralampos Pozidis</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evangelos_S._Eleftheriou\">Evangelos Eleftheriou</a> (<b>2016</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/7428956\">Multilevel-Cell Phase-Change Memory: A Viable Technology</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.org/db/journals/esticas/esticas6.html\">IEEE Journal of Emerging and Selected Topics in Circuits and Systems, Vol. 6</a>, No. 1</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Milos Stanisavljevic</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=a7g7yY8AAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Thomas Mittelholzer</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pers/hd/p/Papandreou:Nikolaos\">Nikolaos Papandreou</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.org/pers/hd/p/Parnell:Thomas_P=\">Thomas P. Parnell</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.co.uk/citations?user=FhioCGgAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Haralampos Pozidis</a> (<b>2018</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/8351740\">Drift-Invariant Detection for Multilevel Phase-Change Memory</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.org/db/conf/iscas/iscas2018.html#StanisavljevicM18\">ISCAS 2018</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Milos_Stanisavljevic&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2009\">2009</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Milos_Stanisavljevic&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: 2009\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=306314&amp;t=30826\">Re: I am feeling ill</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Milos Stanisavljevic</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 01, 2009</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=306463&amp;t=30826\">Re: Why the Campaign vs RYBKA is Biased</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Milos Stanisavljevic</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 01, 2009</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=313387&amp;t=31329\">Re: Smooth scaling stockfish</a> by  <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Milos Stanisavljevic</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 30, 2009</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=313560&amp;t=31361\">Re: Smooth scaling -- an explanation</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Milos Stanisavljevic</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 30, 2009</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010\">2010</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Milos_Stanisavljevic&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: 2010\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=314332&amp;t=31413\">Using Heinz in 2010 is not optimal</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Milos Stanisavljevic</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 01, 2010 </li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=355719&amp;t=34882\">Re: Rybka's magic settings...I think I 've found them</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Milos Stanisavljevic</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, June 13, 2010</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=356417&amp;t=34908\">Re: My recent correspondence with Vasik Rajlich</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Milos Stanisavljevic</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, June 16, 2010</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=361501&amp;t=35415\">Re: Transposition table random numbers</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Milos Stanisavljevic</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 13, 2010</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=362888&amp;t=35455\">Re: Questions for the Stockfish team</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Milos Stanisavljevic</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 20, 2010&#160;» <a href=\"/Evaluation\" title=\"Evaluation\">Evaluation</a>, <a href=\"/Stockf